Rating: 4
Very easy and quite tastey. I used kahlua instead of vanilla to intensify the chocolate flavor, which worked rather nicely. I also whipped up the leftover whipping cream with a little vanilla sugar and kahlua and spread it over the pie with a dusting of cocoa on top. Turned out looking kind of like a Mississippi Mud Pie but with a sophisticated taste and texture. Soooo smooth and creamy, but not to cream cheesey. Very good!!

